Matthias Ginter: Borussia Monchengladbach sign Dortmund defender

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Borussia Monchengladbach have signed Germany defender Matthias Ginter from Borussia Dortmund for a reported 17m euros (Â£14.9m) plus add-ons.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 23-year-old has signed a contract until 2021.
Ginter was part of the Germany side that beat Chile 1-0 in Sunday's Confederations Cup final.
Dortmund's sporting director Michael Zorc said Ginter had "expressed his desire to leave" because of competition for places in the Dortmund squad.
